                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/9.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Blocker</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">J American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Porfirio Diaz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have been informed that Jesus Carranza demands by four p.m. to-day $50,000 gold
                    from Agujita Mining Company. Controlling interests is foreign. Have protested
                    but with small success.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. P. Blocker</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
